history.content:
Your Cal Central is where it's listed, so it sounds like things are great!

You just need to be sure you have nothing outstanding. Believe it or not, students degrees can be delayed due to overdue library books or fines.

Hello, I am wondering if there is any way to see if I am on the degree list. I am a senior EECS major student, and this summer semester is going to be my last semester. I got a degree check from ESS advisor at the beginning of the spring semester, and CalCentral says my expected graduation is summer 2018.

Are there any other things that I need to check to make sure that I am on the list?
history.subject: Is there any way to check if I am on the degree list?
